communicationSummary: Discussed Q3 budget, interested in AI scoring.
Initial discovery call, needs a follow-up demo.
Successful onboarding session, very satisfied with the platform.
Attended webinar on 'AI in Sales'. Downloaded a whitepaper.
Exchanged several emails about pricing. Seems very interested, waiting for her to confirm a meeting.
Responded to an InMail, asked for our one-pager. Not a priority right now.
Contract renewal discussion. Mentioned interest in our new 'Analytics Pro' feature.
Attended a 1-on-1 demo. Asked very specific technical questions about API integration. High potential.
Filled the 'contact us' form on the website. Generic inquiry about services.
Cold email outreach. Replied that the timing is not right, suggests to check back in 6 months.
Follow-up call after the conference. Budget is approved for next quarter. Asked for a formal quote.
Opened an issue on our public repo to ask about a feature. Not a direct sales lead but shows interest.
Reported a minor bug which is now resolved. Expressed overall satisfaction with our support team's reactivity.
Downloaded our 'Top 10 AI tools' guide from a LinkedIn ad.
Sent an email with a typo from a personal address. Seems like a student or individual researcher.
Wants to understand the ROI of our solution. Sent him a case study. Scheduled a call for next week.
Unresponsive after three follow-up emails. Marked as cold for now.
Renewed their annual plan last quarter. No recent activity.
Met at an industry event. Concerned about data privacy and compliance. Sent our GDPR documentation.
He's evaluating our solution against CompetitorX. Thinks our UI is better but CompetitorX is cheaper.
